  "worthless_belief": [],
  "intermediate_belief": "If I don't meet high standards or succeed in my career, then I am not good enough and others will see me as a failure. I must always achieve to prove my value, otherwise I am letting myself and my family down. My self-worth is directly tied to my professional accomplishments.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I keep failing to get a job, it means I will never be successful and there is no point in trying. My efforts are useless, and nothing I do will change my situation.",
  "coping_strategies": "Rachel tends to withdraw and avoid social interactions or job search activities when faced with setbacks, such as a job rejection. She seeks reassurance from her sister Emma, which provides temporary relief but does not address her underlying beliefs or distress. She also ruminates on her perceived failures, repeatedly thinking about her shortcomings instead of taking constructive action.",
  "situation": "Received a job rejection email while searching for work.",
  "auto_thought": "I'm never going to get hired. This just proves I'm not good enough.",
